quran[7]{c,v,t,f}:
  13,6,"They ask you to hasten the evil before the good, while (many) exemplary punishments have indeed occurred before them. But verily, your Lord is full of Forgiveness for mankind in spite of their wrong-doing. And verily, your Lord is (also) Severe in punishment."
  13,7,"And the disbelievers say: "Why is not a sign sent down to him from his Lord?" You are only a warner, and to every people there is a guide."
  13,8,"Allâh knows what every female bears, and by how much the wombs fall short (of their time or number) or exceed. Everything with Him is in (due) proportion."
  13,9,"All-Knower of the Unseen and the seen, the Most Great, the Most High."
  13,10,"It is the same (to Him) whether any of you conceal his speech or declares it openly, whether he be hid by night or goes forth freely by day."